description:
A "fireside chat" with author and financial advisor William Bernstein and Wall Street Journal columnist Jason Zweig, taped at the Bogleheads conference in Oct. 2022. They discuss pivotal events during their careers, behavioral finance and neuroscience, asset allocation, and the biggest mistakes that investors make.

Recorded on October 13, 2022.

(No slides were presented.)

The complete Bogleheads Conference proceedings can be found at https://boglecenter.net/2022conference/

A ten-part YouTube course on the Bogleheads investing principles can be found at https://boglecenter.net/bogleheads-university/. Slides and transcripts are available.

The John C. Bogle Center for Financial Literacy (https://boglecenter.net/) is a non-profit organization dedicated to improving financial literacy.

The Center’s mission is to expand the legacy of John C. Bogle, the founder of Vanguard, by promoting the principles of successful investing and financial well-being through education and community.

The Center envisions a world of well-informed, capable, and empowered investors.

Community outreach is achieved through the Bogleheads forum, wiki, and blog, as well as in-person and virtual Bogleheads chapters worldwide.
